headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had 35 points, a season-high 21 assists and 14 rebounds for his NBA-leading 16th triple-double, helping the Washington Wizards to a 132-124 win over the Indiana Pacers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook records 16th triple-double, Wizards beat Pacers

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 28 points and the New Orleans Pelicans held on after blowing most of a 17-point, fourth-quarter lead to beat Boston 115-109 on Monday night in the Celtics' first game in front of their home fans since before the pandemic.

— James Harden had 38 points, 13 assists and 11 rebounds, already tying the Nets' single-season record with his 12th triple-double in just 32 games, and Brooklyn held off the Minnesota Timberwolves 112-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden has triple-double, Irving 27 as Nets edge Wolves

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 27 points and the Miami Heat snapped a six-game losing streak with a 98-88 win over the New York Knicks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat snap a 6-game losing streak with 98-88 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Saben Lee scored 14 of his 19 points in the first half in his second career start, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Toronto Raptors 118-104 on Monday night.
— Jonas Valanciunas scored a season-high 30 points, including eight down the stretch, to help the Memphis Grizzlies outlast the Houston Rockets 120-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas has season-best 30 points, Griz beat Rockets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 25 points to help the Dallas Mavericks roll past the Oklahoma City Thunder 127-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 25; Mavericks roll past Thunder 127-106

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 24 points, Richaun Holmes had 23 points and 12 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings beat the San Antonio Spurs 132-115 on Monday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Holmes lead Kings by Spurs for 5th straight victory

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 19 points and Rudy Gobert added 18 points and 17 rebounds to power the Utah Jazz to their sixth straight win, a 114-75 victory over Cleveland on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz run win streak to 6 games with 114-75 win over Cavs

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry made a triumphant return from a five-game absence with a bruised tailbone to score 32 points with six 3-pointers, and the Golden State Warriors snapped a four-game losing streak by beating the Chicago Bulls 116-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry returns with 32 points, Warriors beat Bulls 116-102

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris scored 25 points and three other starters had at least 20 points, helping the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Milwaukee Bucks 129-105 on Monday night for their sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers hit 19 3s, beat Bucks 129-105 for 6th win in a row
